 her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde von Dinslaken was born about 1195 as the daughter of Antonius Van Dinslaken and Agnes Von Wangen. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Dietrich VI. von Kleve. She died in 1224, at the age of 30."},"et":{"circa 1195–1224":"umbes 1195–1224","1195–1224":"1195–1224","1185–1260":"1185–1260","1214–1245":"1214–1245","1217–1251":"1217–1251","–Male":"Surnud","1152–1226":"1152–1226","1217":"1217","1226":"1226","about 1210 to 1214":"umbes 1214","1214":"1214","1224":"1224","circa 1195":"umbes 1195","1245":"1245","1152":"1152","1251":"1251","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1260":"1260","Kleve, Rhineland, Prussia, Germany":"Kleve, Rheinprovinz, Freistaat Preußen, Saksamaa","Herzogtum Kleve, Heiliges Römisches Reich":"Kleve"},"fi":{"circa 1195–1224":"noin 1195–1224","1195–1224":"1195–1224","1185–1260":"1185–1260","1214–1245":"1214–1245","1217–1251":"1217–1251","–Male":"Kuollut","1152–1226":"1152–1226","1217":"1217","1226":"1226","about 1210 to 1214":"noin 1214","1214":"1214","1224":"1224","circa 1195":"noin 1195","1245":"1245","1152":"1152","1251":"1251","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1260":"1260","Kleve, Rhineland, Prussia, Germany":"Kleve, Rheinprovinz, Freistaat Preußen, Saksa","Herzogtum Kleve, Heiliges Römisches Reich":"Kleve"},"fr":{"circa 1195–1224":"environ 1195–1224","1195–1224":"1195–1224","1185–1260":"1185–1260","1214–1245":"1214–1245","1217–1251":"1217–1251","–Male":"Décédé","1152–1226":"1152–1226","1217":"1217","1226":"1226","about 1210 to 1214":"environ 1214","1214":"1214","1224":"1224","circa 1195":"environ 1195","1245":"1